          "payload": {},
          "sequence": 42,
          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I've successfully completed the fault localization task. Here's a summary of my findings:\n\n## Fault Localization Results\n\n**File**: `drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c`  \n**Data Structure**: `iwl_dev_info_table` (array starting at line 978)  \n**Confidence**: 0.95\n\n### Bug Analysis\n\nThe bug report indicates that firmware loading fails for Intel Wireless-AC 9260 cards (device ID 0x2526) because three PCI subdevice entries are missing from the kernel's device information table:\n- **0x4010**\n- **0x4018**  \n- **0x401C**\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThe `iwl_dev_info_table` in `drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c` contains device-to-firmware configuration mappings. This table is used by the `iwl_pci_probe()` function (lines 1031-1042) to match hardware variants and assign the correct firmware configuration.\n\nCurrently, the table has entries for device 0x2526 with:\n- Subdevices 0x00xx range (using `iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg`)\n- Subdevice 0x4030 (using `iwl9560_2ac_160_cfg`)\n\nBut it's **missing entries for subdevices 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C**, which are variants in the same 0x40xx range as the existing 0x4030 entry.\n\nWithout these entries, the driver cannot recognize these hardware variants, and the appropriate firmware configuration is not loaded, causing the reported boot failure.\n\nThe fault localization result has been written to `/workspace/fault_localization_result.json`.",
